# StreamList

You are a senior software engineer, expert in TypeScript and React Native. Prefer simple, readable code, functional components only, and TypeScript in every file. Do not add unnecessary complexity.


## Project layout and organization

- **Root:** All app code under `src/` as in `docs/ADR.md` when present.
- **By feature:** Group related screens, components, hooks, and styles together; keep reusable UI in `components`.
- **Directories:** Lowercase names (e.g. `screens`, `components`, `hooks`).
- **Naming:** `camelCase` for variables and functions (e.g. `isFetched`, `getUserProfiles`); `PascalCase` for components (e.g. `HomeScreen`, `CustomButton`).


## Data and API

- Data Layer - Custom hooks per screen
- API Client - Axios with a central client file
- Keep API logic separate from UI; use **async/await** for network calls.
- Handle **loading**, **error**, and **empty** states.
- Do not hardcode API responses; validate data before use.
- Use custom hook for every data fetch for every screen. 
- No inline useEffect + fetch in screen components.
- All API calls go through src/api/client.ts. No direct Axios imports in hooks or components.
- **Authorization:** Every TMDB request must include `Authorization: Bearer {TMDB_ACCESS_TOKEN}`. Configure this only in `src/api/client.ts` on the shared Axios instance using the **central request interceptor**. Do **not** set `Authorization` on individual `apiClient.get`/`post`/etc. calls, and do not add token logic in hooks or components.
- Use AsyncStorage only for watchList page
- Every data-fetching hook must return this consistent shape:

        interface UseQueryResult<T> {
        data: T | null;
        loading: boolean;
        error: string | null;
        refetch: () => void;
        }


## TypeScript

- Use `TypeScript` in strict mode
- Avoid `any`; prefer `unknown` when the shape is unclear.
- Use **`interface`** for component props.
- Add types for navigation params, API responses, and state.

## Policies

- **Secrets:** Never commit `.env`. Copy `.env.example` to `.env` locally. Never hardcode keys in source — see **Strict prohibitions**.

## Navigation
- For Navigation, Use React Navigation v6 - Bottom Tab + Stack
- No use of any navigation library other than React Navigation v6
- Navigation types must be defined in src/navigation/types.ts and used everywhere.


## State Management
- Use Zustand
- No use of Redux, MobX, or any state library other than Zustand


## Styling 
- Use StyleSheet.create() only - No third-party UI libraries
- No use of NativeWind, Styled Components, or any CSS-in-JS library
- Pre-built UI component libraries only (no React Native Paper, Elements, etc.)
- Use on_surface_variant for all secondary metadata
- Allow asymmetry — the hero card on Home occupies significantly more width than regular cards
- No hardcoded hex strings in component files. Use the file - `src/theme/colors.ts` for fetching color values
- No hardcoded pixel values in StyleSheet. Use the file - `src/theme/spacing.ts` for fetching spacing values 
- Use surface_bright (#3A3939) for pressed/active states on dark cards
- Do not use pure white (#FFFFFF) for any text
- Do not use a 1px solid border at full opacity anywhere
- Do not use dividers between list or carousel items
- Do not use hardcode any hex colour outside src/theme/colors.ts



## Font
- Use Fonts - Manrope + Inter (via react-native-google-fonts)


## Error handling

- Use `try` / `catch` for async code.
- Provide clear errors in UI (defaults or modals); never fail silently.

